<subSubSection id="4A20541663F5AD657EF702F5E186ECA8" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph id="82BFCF0F7CA8C7235287CDA2B5F1219D" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
Genus 
<taxonomicName id="75A84CC13808F9541CE2E1F029C808CF" LSID="4CC8AFE9-C3CE-576F-8F6F-FAD96C74AA91" authority="Thorell, 1881" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1881" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Angaeus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Angaeus" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Angaeus Thorell, 1881</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="2A040298B7F97A5B9403379836DC3070" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" type="comments">
<paragraph id="479FE88B12A55C5CE970DC1C2E761A62" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Comments.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="85DC2A7E5AA27EF6289B873C4F19E6C0" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">
This genus includes 11 species, mainly distributed in tropical Asia (India, Malaysia (Borneo), Myanmar, Vietnam, Singapore, and Indonesia) (
<bibRefCitation id="431CF55CDC86B99215D65B8C322D5354" author="World Spider Catalog" journalOrPublisher="Oriental Insects" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" publicationUrl="https://wsc.nmbe.ch/" refId="B24" refString="World Spider Catalog, 2022. World Spider Catalog. Natural History Museum Bern. Version 22.5. https://wsc.nmbe.ch/" title="World Spider Catalog. Natural History Museum Bern. Version 22.5." url="https://wsc.nmbe.ch/" year="2022">WSC 2022</bibRefCitation>
). More than half of these species are recorded from China and have been revised by 
<bibRefCitation id="5F5F0747F6BC2E2E63F391FAA6E94A71" DOI="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3635.1.7" author="Benjamin, SP" journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" pagination="71 - 80" refId="B2" refString="Benjamin, SP, 2013. On the crab spider genus Angaeus Thorell, 1881 and its junior synonym Paraborboropactus Tang and Li, 2009 (Araneae: Thomisidae). Zootaxa 3635 (1): 71 - 80, DOI: https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3635.1.7" title="On the crab spider genus Angaeus Thorell, 1881 and its junior synonym Paraborboropactus Tang and Li, 2009 (Araneae: Thomisidae)." url="https://doi.org/10.11646/zootaxa.3635.1.7" volume="3635" year="2013">Benjamin (2013)</bibRefCitation>
. It is worth mentioning that the female of the type species, 
<taxonomicName id="E29CECDB077C18ACC70263D20BF9218C" authorityName="Thorell" authorityYear="1881" class="Arachnida" family="Thomisidae" genus="Angaeus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Angaeus pudicus" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="43" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pudicus">
<emphasis id="E8602363B5AC461A155665C98BD52ED3" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="43">Angaeus pudicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Thorell, 1881, remains unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
